‚ÄúNanotechnology is fundamental to North Carolina‚Äôs economic development strategy of growing jobs and building a new economy,‚Äù Perdue said. ‚ÄúAs one of the top 10 nanotech states, North Carolina will continue to push ahead and lead a technology sector that will change every industry and create products that will change the way we live.‚Äù

The data was released by the Project on Emerging Technologies and features more than 1,200 organizations across the United States that are part of the nanotechnology industry.† North Carolina joins California, Massachusetts, New York and Texas as one of the top 10 states.

